HEADWORD: Polyscope
<hw>Pol"y*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
farseeing; <grk>poly`s</grk> much, many + <?/ to view: cf. F.
<ets>polyscope</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>A glass
which makes a single object appear as many; a multiplying glass.</def>
<rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An apparatus for affording a view
of the different cavities of the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polysepalous</ent>⟦br⟧
